snippet: Oregon will have to face Ohio State in Monday’s title game without wide receiver Darren Carrington and running back Ayele Forde.
abstract: Oregon wide receiver Darren Carrington and running back Ayele Forde will miss inaugural College Football Playoff championship game against Ohio State after their drug tests come back positive.
lead_paragraph: Oregon will have to face Ohio State in Monday’s title game without wide receiver Darren Carrington and running back Ayele Forde.

headline.main: Two Ducks Are Out After Positive Drug Tests
headline.print_headline: Two Ducks Are Out After Positive Drug Tests
